Id.description: Globally unique string that identifies a record.

LastName.title: Last Name
LastName.description: Concatenation of FirstName, MiddleName, LastName, and Suffix up to 203 characters, including whitespaces.

FirstName.title: First Name
FirstName.description: Concatenation of FirstName, MiddleName, LastName, and Suffix up to 203 characters, including whitespaces.

Salutation.title: Salutation
Salutation.description: Concatenation of FirstName, MiddleName, LastName, and Suffix up to 203 characters, including whitespaces.

Name.title: Full Name
Name.description: Concatenation of FirstName, MiddleName, LastName, and Suffix up to 203 characters, including whitespaces.

Title.title: Title
Title.description: Title for the lead, such as CFO or CEO. The maximum size is 128 characters. When converting a lead to a person account, the coversion fails if the lead Title field contains more than 80 characters.

Company.title: Company
Company.description: Required. The lead’s company. Note If person account record types have been enabled, and if the value of Company is null, the lead converts to a person account.

Street.title: Street
Street.description: The compound form of the address. Read-only. For details on compound address fields, see Address Compound Fields.

City.title: City
City.description: The compound form of the address. Read-only. For details on compound address fields, see Address Compound Fields.

State.title: State/Province
State.description: The compound form of the address. Read-only. For details on compound address fields, see Address Compound Fields.

PostalCode.title: Zip/Postal Code
PostalCode.description: The compound form of the address. Read-only. For details on compound address fields, see Address Compound Fields.

Country.title: Country
Country.description: The compound form of the address. Read-only. For details on compound address fields, see Address Compound Fields.

StateCode.title: State/Province Code
StateCode.description: The compound form of the address. Read-only. For details on compound address fields, see Address Compound Fields.

CountryCode.title: Country Code
CountryCode.description: The compound form of the address. Read-only. For details on compound address fields, see Address Compound Fields.

Latitude.title: Latitude
Latitude.description: The compound form of the address. Read-only. For details on compound address fields, see Address Compound Fields.

Longitude.title: Longitude
Longitude.description: The compound form of the address. Read-only. For details on compound address fields, see Address Compound Fields.

GeocodeAccuracy.title: Geocode Accuracy
GeocodeAccuracy.description: The compound form of the address. Read-only. For details on compound address fields, see Address Compound Fields.

Address.title: Address
Address.description: The compound form of the address. Read-only. For details on compound address fields, see Address Compound Fields.

Status.title: Status
Status.description: Status code for this converted lead. Status codes are defined in Status and represented in the API by the LeadStatus object.

Industry.title: Industry
Industry.description: Industry in which the lead works.

CurrencyIsoCode.title: Lead Currency
CurrencyIsoCode.description: Available only for organizations with the multicurrency feature enabled. Contains the ISO code for any currency allowed by the organization.

AnnualRevenue.title: Annual Revenue
AnnualRevenue.description: Annual revenue for the lead’s company.

NumberOfEmployees.title: Employees
NumberOfEmployees.description: Number of employees at the lead’s company. Label is Employees.

HasOptedOutOfEmail.title: Email Opt Out
HasOptedOutOfEmail.description: Indicates whether the lead doesn’t want to receive email from Salesforce (true) or does (false). Label is Email Opt Out.

IsConverted.title: Converted
IsConverted.description: Indicates whether the lead has been converted (true) or not (false). Label is Converted.

ConvertedDate.title: Converted Date
ConvertedDate.description: Date on which this lead was converted.

IsUnreadByOwner.title: Unread By Owner
IsUnreadByOwner.description: If true, lead has been assigned, but not yet viewed. See Unread Leads for more information. Label is Unread By Owner.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

LastActivityDate.title: Last Activity
LastActivityDate.description: Value is the most recent of either: Due date of the most recent event logged against the record. Due date of the most recently closed task associated with the record.

HasOptedOutOfFax.title: Fax Opt Out
HasOptedOutOfFax.description: Indicates whether the lead doesn’t want to receive faxes from Salesforce (true) or does (false). Label is FaxOpt Out.

Jigsaw.title: Data.com Key
Jigsaw.description: References the ID of a contact in Data.com. If a lead has a value in this field, it means that a contact was imported as a lead from Data.com. If the contact (converted to a lead) wasn’t imported from Data.com, the field value is null. Maximum size is 20 characters. Available in API version 22.0 and later. Label is Data.com Key. Important The Jigsawfield is exposed in the API to support troubleshooting for import errors and reimporting of corrected data. Don’t modify the value in the Jigsaw field.

EmailBouncedReason.title: Email Bounced Reason
EmailBouncedReason.description: If bounce management is activated and an email sent to the lead bounced, the reason for the bounce.

EmailBouncedDate.title: Email Bounced Date
EmailBouncedDate.description: If bounce management is activated and an email sent to the lead bounced, the date and time of the bounce.

Pronouns.title: Pronouns
Pronouns.description: The lead’s personal pronouns, reflecting their gender identity. Others can use these pronouns to refer to the lead in the third person. The entry is selected from a picklist of available values, which the administrator sets. Maximum 40 characters.

GenderIdentity.title: Gender Identity
GenderIdentity.description: The lead’s internal experience of their gender, which may or may not correspond to their designated sex at birth.

schema.description: [Core] Represents a product entry (an association between a Pricebook2 and Product2) in a price book.

Id.title: Price Book Entry ID
Id.description: Globally unique string that identifies a record.

Name.title: Product Name
Name.description: Name of this PricebookEntry record. This read-only field references the value in the Name field of the Product2 record. Label is Product Name.

CurrencyIsoCode.title: Currency ISO Code
CurrencyIsoCode.description: Available only for organizations with the multicurrency feature enabled. Contains the ISO code for any currency allowed by the organization.

UnitPrice.title: List Price
UnitPrice.description: Required. Unit price for this price book entry. You can specify a value only if UseStandardPrice is set to false. Label is List Price.

IsActive.title: Active
IsActive.description: Indicates whether this price book entry is active (true) or not (false). Although you can never delete PricebookEntry records, your client application can set this flag to false. Inactive PricebookEntry records are hidden in many areas in the user interface. You can change this flag on a PricebookEntry record as often as necessary.

UseStandardPrice.title: Use Standard Price
UseStandardPrice.description: Indicates whether this price book entry uses the standard price defined in the standard Pricebook2 record (true) or not (false). If set to true, then the UnitPrice field is read-only, and the value is the same as the UnitPrice value in the corresponding PricebookEntry in the standard price book (that is, the PricebookEntry record whose Pricebook2Id refers to the standard price book and whose Product2Id and CurrencyIsoCode are the same as this record). For PricebookEntry records associated with the standard Pricebook2 record, this field must be set to true.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

ProductCode.title: Product Code
ProductCode.description: Product code for this record. This read-only field references the value in the ProductCode field of the associated Product2 record.

IsArchived.title: Archived
IsArchived.description: Indicates whether the PricebookEntry has been archived (true) or not (false). This field is set to true when the Product2 record it’s associated with is archived, or when the Pricebook2 record is archived. This field is read only. Available in API version 45.0 and later. Label is Archived.

ActivePriceAdjustmentQuantity.title: Active Price Adjustments
ActivePriceAdjustmentQuantity.description: The count of active price adjustment schedules associated with the price book entry. This field is available in API version 49.0 and later.

schema.description: [Core] Represents a product that your company sells.

Id.title: Product ID
Id.description: Globally unique string that identifies a record.

Name.title: Product Name
Name.description: Required. Default name of this record. Label is Product Name.

ProductCode.title: Product Code
ProductCode.description: Default product code for this record. Your org defines the product’s code-naming pattern.

Description.title: Product Description
Description.description: A text description of this record. Label is Product Description.

CanUseQuantitySchedule.title: Quantity Scheduling Enabled
CanUseQuantitySchedule.description: Indicates whether the product can have a quantity schedule (true) or not (false). Label is Quantity Scheduling Enabled.

CanUseRevenueSchedule.title: Revenue Scheduling Enabled
CanUseRevenueSchedule.description: Indicates whether the product can have a revenue schedule (true) or not (false). Label is Revenue Scheduling Enabled.

IsActive.title: Active
IsActive.description: Indicates whether this record is active (true) or not (false). Inactive Product2 records are hidden in many areas in the user interface. You can change the IsActive flag on a Product2 object as often as necessary. Label is Active.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

Family.title: Product Family
Family.description: Name of the product family associated with this record. Product families are configured as picklists in the user interface. To obtain a list of valid values, call describeSObjects() and process the result for the values associated with the Family field. Label is Product Family.

IsSerialized.title: Serialized
IsSerialized.description: Indicates if a product is a serialized product (true) or not (false). Label is Serialized.

CurrencyIsoCode.title: Currency ISO Code
CurrencyIsoCode.description: Available only for orgs with the multicurrency feature enabled. Contains the ISO code for any currency allowed by the org.

ExternalId.title: External ID
ExternalId.description: The unique identifier of a record in the linked external data source. For example, ID #123.

DisplayUrl.title: Display URL
DisplayUrl.description: URL leading to a specific version of a record in the linked external data source.

QuantityUnitOfMeasure.title: Quantity Unit Of Measure
QuantityUnitOfMeasure.description: Unit of the product; for example, kilograms, liters, or cases. This field comes with only one value, Each, so consider creating your own. The QuantityUnitOfMeasure field on ProductItem inherits this field’s values.

IsArchived.title: Archived
IsArchived.description: Describes whether the product is archived. The default value is false.

StockKeepingUnit.title: Product SKU
StockKeepingUnit.description: The SKU for the product. Use in tandem with or instead of the ProductCode field. For example, you can track the manufacturer’s identifying code in the Product Code field and assign the product a SKU when you resell it.

Type.title: Product Type
Type.description: The type of product. This field's value affects the read-only value of the ProductClassfield on the Product2 object. field. Base—When Type = Base, then ProductClass = VariationParent. Null—When Type = Null, then ProductClass = Simple. This field is available when B2B or B2C Commerce is enabled. This field is available in API version 50.0 and later.

ProductClass.title: Product Class
ProductClass.description: This field is read-only. Its value is determined by the value of the Type field and whether the product is associated with a ProductAttribute record. It describes whether a product is a simple product, a variation parent, or a product variation. Possible values are: Simple—This product has no variations VariationParent—This product is a variation parent. It’s the base product for one or more product variations and, though it has its own stock-keeping unit (SKU), isn’t a sellable entity. Instead, it’s the parent of sellable entities—its variations. Variation—This product is a variation of a parent product. Each variation has its own SKU. When the value of ProductClass = VariationParent, it never changes. The value of ProductClass changes between Simple and Variation when you attach or detach a ProductAttribute record to the product. If you attach a ProductAttribute record to a product, then the product’s ProductClass value changes to Variation. Conversely, when you detach all ProductAttribute records from a product, the ProductClass value changes to Simple. The default value is Simple. This field is available in API version 50.0 and later. It was introduced to support of B2B and B2C Commerce implementations.

TransferRecordMode.title: Transfer Record Mode
TransferRecordMode.description: If serialized, indicates when the serial number is recorded. This field is visible based on field-level security.

ConfigureDuringSale.title: Configure During Sale
ConfigureDuringSale.description: Determines whether a user can edit a configuration when creating a bundle order or quote.

IsSoldOnlyWithOtherProds.title: Sell only with other products
IsSoldOnlyWithOtherProds.description: Determines whether the product can be sold independently or only as part of a bundle.

schema.description: [Sales Cloud] Represents a quote line item, which is a member of the list of Product2 products associated with a Quote, along with other information about those line items on that quote.

Id.title: Quote Line Item ID
Id.description: Globally unique string that identifies a record.

CurrencyIsoCode.title: Currency ISO Code
CurrencyIsoCode.description: Available only for organizations enabled for multiple currencies. Contains the ISO code for any currency allowed by the organization. If the organization has multicurrency and a Pricebook2 is specified on the quote (the Pricebook2Id field isn’t blank), then the currency value of this field must match the currency of the PricebookEntry objects for any associated quote line items.This value is copied from the related Quote and can't be changed.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

Quantity.title: Quantity
Quantity.description: Required. The number of units for the line item.

UnitPrice.title: Sales Price
UnitPrice.description: Required. The price per unit for the quote line item.

HasRevenueSchedule.title: Has Revenue Schedule
HasRevenueSchedule.description: Read-only. Indicates whether the opportunity line item that the quote line item is synced with has a revenue schedule. If this object has a revenue schedule, the GrandTotal and TotalPrice fields can't be updated. In addition, the Quantity field can't be updated if this object has a quantity schedule. The system ignores any attempt to update this field. The update isn't rejected but the updated value is ignored.

HasQuantitySchedule.title: Has Quantity Schedule
HasQuantitySchedule.description: Read-only. Indicates whether the opportunity line item that the quote line item is synced with has a quantity schedule.

Description.title: Line Item Description
Description.description: Text description of the line item. Limit: 225 characters.

ServiceDate.title: Date
ServiceDate.description: Date when the product revenue is recognized and the product quantity will be shipped.

SortOrder.title: Sort Order
SortOrder.description: The value of where the line item is in the sorted order, such as 1, 2, 3. The SortOrder value determines the order in which a quote line item displays in the Quote Line Items related list and the Quote PDF. Client applications can use this value to match the sort order in Salesforce. This field is only available in API versions 21.0 and greater.

NetUnitPrice.title: Net Unit Price
NetUnitPrice.description: The unit price after all price adjustments are applied.

NetTotalPrice.title: Net Total Price
NetTotalPrice.description: The price after all adjustments, inclusive of quantity, prorated for the duration of the subscription. This field is a calculated field equal to TotalAdjustmentAmount plus TotalLineAmount.This field is available in API version 56.0 and later. This field is available with Subscription Management.

SellingModelType.title: Selling Model Type
SellingModelType.description: Indicates whether the quote line item is sold as one-time purchase, an evergreen subscription, or as a termed subscription. This field is available in API version 55.0 and later. This field is available with Subscription Management.

PricingTerm.title: Pricing Term
PricingTerm.description: The number of terms in the subscription. For example, if a monthly subscription is priced yearly, this field is 12. This field is available in API version 55.0 and later. This field is available with Subscription Management.

PricingTermUnit.title: Pricing Term Unit
PricingTermUnit.description: The unit of time for the pricing term. This field is available in API version 55.0 and later. This field is available with Subscription Management.

BillingFrequency.title: Billing Frequency
BillingFrequency.description: The time period that indicates how often the quote line item is billed. This field is available in API version 55.0 and later. This field is available when Subscription Management is enabled.

HasSchedule.title: Schedule
HasSchedule.description: Read-only. Indicates whether the line item uses schedules.

ListPrice.title: List Price
ListPrice.description: Read-only. Corresponds to the UnitPrice on the PricebookEntry that is associated with this line item, which can be in the standard price book or a custom price book. A client application can use this information to show whether the unit price (or sales price) of the line item differs from the price book entry list price.

Subtotal.title: Subtotal
Subtotal.description: The line item's Quantity multiplied by the UnitPrice.

TotalPrice.title: Total Price
TotalPrice.description: Read-only. Calculated by applying the Discount to the Subtotal. This field is nillable, but you can't set both TotalPrice and UnitPrice to null in the same update. To insert the TotalPrice for a quote line item via the API (given only a unit price and the quantity), calculate this field as the unit price multiplied by the quantity. This field is read-only if the quote line item has a revenue schedule.

TotalTaxAmount.title: Total Tax Amount
TotalTaxAmount.description: the total amount of tax for the quote line item. his field is available in API version 55.0 and later. This field is available with Subscription Management.

TotalPriceWithTax.title: Total Price with Tax
TotalPriceWithTax.description: The sum of TotalPrice and TotalTaxAmount. This field is available in API version 55.0 and later. This field is available with Subscription Management.

StartDate.title: Start Date
StartDate.description: If the quote line item is sold on subscription, this field indicates the date on which the subscription starts. This field is available in API version 55.0 and later. This field is available with Subscription Management.

EndDate.title: End Date
EndDate.description: If the quote line item is sold on subscription, this field indicates the date on which the subscription ends. This field is available in API version 55.0 and later. This field is available if Subscription Management is enabled in your org.You can indicate a subscription’s length using either StartDate and EndDate, or by using StartDate and SubscriptionTerm. If you provide a value for both EndDate and SubscriptionTerm, EndDate is used to determine the subscription’s length.

SubscriptionTerm.title: Subscription Term
SubscriptionTerm.description: The number of terms in the subscription.You can indicate a subscription’s length using either StartDate and EndDate, or by using StartDate and SubscriptionTerm. If you provide a value for both EndDate and SubscriptionTerm, EndDate is used and SubscriptionTerm is ignored.

SubscriptionTermUnit.title: Subscription Term Unit
SubscriptionTermUnit.description: The unit of time used to define the subscription. This field is available in API version 55.0 and later. This field is available with Subscription Management.

PricingTermCount.title: Pricing Term Count
PricingTermCount.description: A calculated field indicating the number of pricing terms in the subscription. This field is available in API version 55.0 and later. This field is available with Subscription Management.

PeriodBoundary.title: Period Boundary
PeriodBoundary.description: The period boundary helps determine the start and end date of the billing periods. This field is available in API version 55.0 and later. This field is available with Subscription Management.

PeriodBoundaryDay.title: Period Boundary Day
PeriodBoundaryDay.description: Required when PeriodBoundary is DayOfPeriod. Indicates day of the week or month that marks the period boundary. Must be an integer from 1 through 31.This field is available in API version 55.0 and later. This field is available with Subscription Management.

TotalLineAmount.title: Total Line Amount
TotalLineAmount.description: The total price of the quote line item, before price adjustments, inclusive of quantity, prorated for the duration of the subscription. This price is a calculated field equal to TotalPrice times Quantity times PricingTermCount.This field is available in API version 56.0 and later. This field is available with Subscription Management.

TotalAdjustmentAmount.title: Total Adjustment Amount
TotalAdjustmentAmount.description: The sum of the adjustments applied to the quote line item, inclusive of quantity, prorated for the duration of the subscription. This field is available in API version 56.0 and later. This field is available with Subscription Management.

PeriodBoundaryStartMonth.title: Period Boundary Start Month
PeriodBoundaryStartMonth.description: Field is populated based on input in the StartDate, PeriodBoundary, and PeriodBoundaryDay when BillingFrequency is Annual and PricingTermUnit is Annual or by manual user entry. Possible values are: 1-January 2-February 3-March 4-April 5-May 6-June 7-July 8-August 9-September 10-October 11-November 12-December

schema.description: [Core] Represents a price book that contains the list of products that your org sells.

Id.title: Price Book ID
Id.description: Globally unique string that identifies a record.

Name.title: Price Book Name
Name.description: Required. Name of this object. This field is read-only for the standard price book. Label is Price Book Name.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

IsActive.title: Active
IsActive.description: Indicates whether the price book is active (true) or not (false). Inactive price books are hidden in many areas in the user interface. You can change this field’s value as often as necessary. Label is Active.

IsArchived.title: Archived
IsArchived.description: Indicates whether the price book has been archived (true) or not (false). This field is read only.

Description.title: Description
Description.description: Text description of the price book.

IsStandard.title: Is Standard Price Book
IsStandard.description: Indicates whether the price book is the standard price book for the org (true) or not (false). Every org has one standard price book—all other price books are custom price books.

ValidFrom.title: Valid From
ValidFrom.description: The date and time when a Commerce price book is initially valid. If this field is null, the price book is valid immediately when active. Available in API version 48.0 and later.

ValidTo.title: Valid To
ValidTo.description: The date and time when a Commerce price book is valid to. If this field is null, the price book is valid until it’s deactivated. Available in API version 48.0 and later.

This value is copied from the related Opportunity and can't be changed.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date

QuoteNumber.title: Quote Number

IsSyncing.title: Syncing
IsSyncing.description: Indicates whether the quote is syncing with an opportunity.

ShippingHandling.title: Shipping and Handling
ShippingHandling.description: The total shipping and handling costs for the quote.

Tax.title: Tax

Status.title: Status

ExpirationDate.title: Expiration Date
ExpirationDate.description: The date when this quote is no longer valid.

Description.title: Description
Description.description: Text description of the quote. Limit: 32,000 characters.

Subtotal.title: Subtotal
Subtotal.description: The sum of sales price multiplied by quantity for line items, not including the discount.

TotalPrice.title: Total Price
TotalPrice.description: The total of the quote line items after discounts and before taxes and shipping.

LineItemCount.title: Line Items
LineItemCount.description: The number of line items on the quote.

BillingName.title: Bill To Name
BillingName.description: Entity that the quote is billed to.

ShippingName.title: Ship To Name
ShippingName.description: The name of the entity (such as a person or business) that the quote is sent to for approval.

QuoteToName.title: Quote To Name
QuoteToName.description: The name of the entity (such as a person or business) that the quote is sent to for approval. Limit: 255 characters.

AdditionalName.title: Additional To Name
AdditionalName.description: Name associated with the quote's additional address. Limited: 255 characters.

Email.title: Email
Email.description: The email address of the contact who’s associated with the quote.

Phone.title: Phone
Phone.description: The phone number of the contact who’s associated with the quote.

Fax.title: Fax
Fax.description: The fax number for the contact who’s associated with the quote.

CalculationStatus.title: Calculation Status
CalculationStatus.description: Price calculations are performed by Salesforce. Tax calculations are performed by a third-party tax provider integration with Salesforce. Both of these calculations are asynchronous, and you can use this field to see the status of the asynchronous processes.

TotalTaxAmount.title: Total Tax Amount
TotalTaxAmount.description: The total amount of all taxes. This field is available in API version 55.0 and later. This field is available if Subscription Management is enabled in your org.

TotalPriceWithTax.title: Total Price With Tax
TotalPriceWithTax.description: The sum of TotalPrice and TotalTaxAmount. This field is available in API version 55.0 and later. This field is available if Subscription Management is enabled in your org.

Discount.title: Discount
Discount.description: Difference between the sum of the QuoteLineItem record'sSubtotal and the sum of the QuoteLineItem record's Discount totals. Expressed as a percentage.

GrandTotal.title: Grand Total
GrandTotal.description: The total price of the quote plus shipping and taxes.

data.description: [Sales Cloud] Represents a quote, which is a record showing proposed prices for products and services.

data.description: [Sales Cloud] Represents an opportunity line item, which is a member of the list of Product2 products associated with an Opportunity.

schema.description: [Sales Cloud] Represents an opportunity line item, which is a member of the list of Product2 products associated with an Opportunity.

Id.title: Line Item ID
Id.description: Globally unique string that identifies a record.

SortOrder.title: Sort Order
SortOrder.description: Number indicating the sort order selected by the user. Client applications can use this to match the sort order in Salesforce.

ProductCode.title: Product Code
ProductCode.description: This read-only field is available in API version 30.0 and later. It references the value in the ProductCode field of the related Product2 record.

Name.title: Opportunity Product Name
Name.description: The opportunity line item name (known as “Opportunity Product” in the user interface). This read-only field is available in API version 30.0 and later.

CurrencyIsoCode.title: Currency ISO Code
CurrencyIsoCode.description: Available only for organizations with the multicurrency feature enabled. Contains the ISO code for any currency allowed by the organization.

Quantity.title: Quantity
Quantity.description: Read-only if this record has a quantity schedule, a revenue schedule, or both a quantity and a revenue schedule.When updating these records: If you specify Quantity without specifying the UnitPrice, the UnitPrice value will be adjusted to accommodate the new Quantity value, and the TotalPrice will be held constant. If you specify both Discount and Quantity, you must also specify either TotalPrice or UnitPrice so the system can determine which one to automatically adjust.

TotalPrice.title: Total Price
TotalPrice.description: This field is available only for backward compatibility. It represents the total price of the OpportunityLineItem.If you do not specify UnitPrice, this field is required. If you specify Discount and Quantity, this field or UnitPrice is required. When updating these records, you can change either this value or the UnitPrice, but not both at the same time. This field is nillable, but you can’t set both TotalPrice and UnitPrice to null in the same update request. To insert the TotalPrice via the API (given only a unit price and the quantity), calculate this field as the unit price multiplied by the quantity. This field is read-only if the opportunity line item has a revenue schedule. If the opportunity line item does not have a schedule or only has quantity schedule, this field can be updated.

UnitPrice.title: Sales Price
UnitPrice.description: The unit price for the opportunity line item. In the Salesforce user interface, this field’s value is calculated by dividing the total price of the opportunity line item by the quantity listed for that line item. Label is Sales Price.This field or TotalPrice is required. You can’t specify both. If you specify Discount and Quantity, this field or TotalPrice is required.

ListPrice.title: List Price
ListPrice.description: Corresponds to the UnitPrice on the PricebookEntry that is associated with this line item, which can be in the standard price book or a custom price book. A client application can use this information to show whether the unit price (or sales price) of the line item differs from the price book entry list price.

ServiceDate.title: Date
ServiceDate.description: Date when the product revenue will be recognized and the product quantity will be shipped. Opportunity Close Date—ServiceDate is ignored. Product Date—ServiceDate is used if not null. Schedule Date—ServiceDate is used if not null and there are no revenue schedules present for this line item, that is, there are no OpportunityLineItemSchedule records with a field Type value of Revenue that are children of this record.

HasRevenueSchedule.title: Has Revenue Schedule
HasRevenueSchedule.description: Indicates whether a revenue schedule has been created for this object (true) or not (false).

HasQuantitySchedule.title: Has Quantity Schedule
HasQuantitySchedule.description: Read-only. Indicates whether a quantity schedule has been created for this object (true) or not (false).

Description.title: Line Description
Description.description: Text description of the opportunity line item. Limit: 255 characters.

HasSchedule.title: Has Schedule
HasSchedule.description: If either HasQuantitySchedule or HasRevenueSchedule is true, this field is also true.

CanUseQuantitySchedule.title: Quantity Scheduling Enabled
CanUseQuantitySchedule.description: Indicates whether the opportunity product can have a quantity schedule (true) or not (false). This field is read-only.

CanUseRevenueSchedule.title: Revenue Scheduling Enabled
CanUseRevenueSchedule.description: Indicates whether the opportunity product can have a revenue schedule (true) or not (false). This field is read-only.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

data.description: [Security&Identity] Represents a user in your organization.

schema.description: [Security&Identity] Represents a user in your organization.

Id.title: User ID
Id.description: Globally unique string that identifies a record.

Username.title: Username
Username.description: Required. Contains the name that a user enters to log in to the API or the user interface. The value for this field must be in the form of an email address, using all lowercase characters. It must also be unique across all organizations. If you try to create or update a User with a duplicate value for this field, the operation is rejected.Each inserted User also counts as a license. Every organization has a maximum number of licenses. If you attempt to exceed the maximum number of licenses by inserting User records, the create request is rejected.

LastName.title: Last Name
LastName.description: Concatenation of FirstName and LastName. Limited to 203 characters, including whitespaces.

FirstName.title: First Name
FirstName.description: Concatenation of FirstName and LastName. Limited to 203 characters, including whitespaces.

Name.title: Full Name
Name.description: Concatenation of FirstName and LastName. Limited to 203 characters, including whitespaces.

CompanyName.title: Company Name
CompanyName.description: The name of the user’s company.

Division.title: Division
Division.description: The division associated with this user, similar to Department, and unrelated to DefaultDivision.

Department.title: Department
Department.description: The company department associated with the user.

Title.title: Title
Title.description: The user’s business title, such as Vice President.

SenderEmail.title: Email Sender Address
SenderEmail.description: The email address used as the From address when the user sends emails. This address is the same value shown in Setup on the My Email Settings page.

SenderName.title: Email Sender Name
SenderName.description: The name used as the email sender when the user sends emails. This name is the same value shown in Setup on the My Email Settings page.

Signature.title: Email Signature
Signature.description: The signature text added to emails. This text is the same value shown in Setup on the My Email Settings page.

Alias.title: Alias
Alias.description: Required. The user’s alias. For example, jsmith.

CommunityNickname.title: Nickname
CommunityNickname.description: Name used to identify this user in the Experience Cloud site.

BadgeText.title: User Photo badge text overlay
BadgeText.description: The Experience Cloud site role, displayed on the user profile page just below the user name.

IsActive.title: Active
IsActive.description: Indicates whether the user has access to log in (true) or not (false). You can modify a User's active status from the user interface or via the API.

TimeZoneSidKey.title: Time Zone
TimeZoneSidKey.description: Required. This field is a restricted picklist field. A User time zone affects the offset used when displaying or entering times in the user interface. But the API doesn’t use a User time zone when querying or setting values.Values for this field are named using region and key city, according to ISO standards. You can also manually set one User time zone in the user interface, and then use that value for creating or updating other User records via the API.

LocaleSidKey.title: Locale
LocaleSidKey.description: Required. This field is a restricted picklist field. The value of the field affects formatting and parsing of values, especially numeric values, in the user interface. It doesn’t affect the API.The field values are named according to the language, and the country if necessary, using two-letter ISO codes. The set of names is based on the ISO standard. You can also manually set a user’s locale in the user interface, and then use that value for inserting or updating other users via the API.

ReceivesInfoEmails.title: Info Emails
ReceivesInfoEmails.description: Indicates whether the user receives informational email from Salesforce (true) or not (false).

ReceivesAdminInfoEmails.title: Admin Info Emails
ReceivesAdminInfoEmails.description: Indicates whether the user receives email for administrators from Salesforce (true) or not (false).

EmailEncodingKey.title: Email Encoding
EmailEncodingKey.description: Required. The email encoding for the user, such as ISO-8859-1 or UTF-8.

DefaultCurrencyIsoCode.title: Default Currency ISO Code
DefaultCurrencyIsoCode.description: The user's default currency setting for new records. For example, if a user in France sets DefaultCurrencyIsoCode to euros, then that’s their default currency.Only applicable for organizations that use multiple currencies.

UserType.title: User Type
UserType.description: The category of user license. Each UserType is associated with one or more UserLicense records. Each UserLicense is associated with one or more profiles. In API version 10.0 and later, valid values include: Standard: user license. This user type also includes Salesforce Platform and Salesforce Platform One user licenses. Label is Standard. PowerPartner: User whose access is limited because they’re a partner and typically access the application through a partner portal or Experience Cloud site. Label is Partner. CspLitePortal: user whose access is limited because they’re an org's customer and access the application through a Customer Portal or Experience Cloud site. Label is High Volume Portal. CustomerSuccess: user whose access is limited because they’re an org's customer and access the application through a Customer Portal. Label is Customer Portal User. PowerCustomerSuccess: user whose access is limited because they’re an org's customer and access the application through a Customer Portal. Label is Customer Portal Manager. Users with this license type can view and edit data they directly own or data owned by or shared with users below them in the Customer Portal role hierarchy. CsnOnly: user whose access to the application is limited to Chatter. This user type includes Chatter Free and Chatter moderator users. Label is Chatter Free. Guest: user whose access is limited because they’re an unauthenticated user without login credentials. Label is Guest.

LanguageLocaleKey.title: Language
LanguageLocaleKey.description: Required. The user’s language, such as French or Chinese (Traditional). Label is Language. Note In API version 47.0 and later, when using the DescribeSObjectResult API to return PicklistEntry values from this picklist, the active value indicates whether the language is in the user’s Displayed Languages (true) or the user’s Available Languages (false). All other languages aren’t in the returned active value array. In API version 46.0 and earlier, the PicklistEntry active values indicate whether the language is in either the user’s Displayed Languages or Available Languages lists (true) or not in either list (false).

ManagerId.title: Manager ID
ManagerId.description: User lookup field used to select the user's manager. This field establishes a hierarchical relationship, preventing you from selecting a user that directly or indirectly reports to themselves.

LastLoginDate.title: Last Login
LastLoginDate.description: The date and time when the user last successfully logged in. This value is updated if 60 seconds elapses since the user’s last login.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

NumberOfFailedLogins.title: Failed Login Attempts
NumberOfFailedLogins.description: The number of failed login attempts for the user’s account. When the maximum number of failed login attempts is reached, the counter resets and the user’s account is locked. If there’s a successful login before the maximum number of failed login attempts is reached, the counter resets and the user’s account remains unlocked.

OfflineTrialExpirationDate.title: Offline Edition Trial Expiration Date
OfflineTrialExpirationDate.description: The date and time when the user’s Connect Offline trial expires.

ForecastEnabled.title: Allow Forecasting
ForecastEnabled.description: Indicates whether the user is enabled for forecasts (true) or not (false). Forecast user have access to the forecasts page.

IsPartner.title: Is Partner
IsPartner.description: Indicates whether the user is a partner who has access to the partner portal (true) or not (false). This field isn’t available for release 9.0 and later. Instead, use UserType with the value Partner or Power Partner.

PortalRole.title: Portal Role Level
PortalRole.description: The role of the user in the Customer Portal (either Executive, Manager, User, or PersonAcount).Prior to API version 16.0, if you set this field to null, the system automatically included a portal role. In API version 16.0 and above, when you set this field to null, a portal role is not automatically created. When this field is null and a ContactId is provided, the user is assigned to the User role. The Update property is available in API version 43.0 and later. The field is available if Customer Portal is enabled OR digital experiences is enabled and Experience Cloud sites have available partner portal, Customer Portal, or High-Volume Portal User licenses.

IsPortalEnabled.title: Is Portal Enabled
IsPortalEnabled.description: Indicates whether an active, external, user has access to Experience Cloud sites or portals (true) or not (false).This field is only available if one of these conditions is true: Digital experiences is enabled and you have community or portal user licenses Portals are enabled Note Users with External Identity licenses can access Experience Cloud sites even if the flag is false.

IsPortalSelfRegistered.title: Self-Registered via Customer Portal
IsPortalSelfRegistered.description: Indicates whether the user is a Customer Portal user who self-registered for your organization's Customer Portal (true) or not (false). This field isn’t available for release 9.0 and earlier.

FederationIdentifier.title: SAML Federation ID
FederationIdentifier.description: Indicates the value that must be listed in the Subject element of a Security Assertion Markup Language (SAML) IDP certificate to authenticate the user for a client application using single sign-on. This value must be specified if the SAML User ID Type is Assertion contains Federation ID from the User record. Otherwise, this field can’t be edited.

AboutMe.title: About Me
AboutMe.description: Information about the user, such as areas of interest or skills. This field is available even if Chatter is disabled.

FullPhotoUrl.title: Url for full-sized Photo
FullPhotoUrl.description: The URL for the user's profile photo. This field is available even if Chatter is disabled.The URL is updated every time a photo is uploaded and reflects the most recent photo. If a newer photo is uploaded, the URL returned for an older photo isn’t guaranteed to return a photo. Query this field for the URL of the most recent photo. This field is available in API version 20.0 and later.

SmallPhotoUrl.title: Photo
SmallPhotoUrl.description: The URL for a thumbnail of the user's profile photo. This field is available even if Chatter is disabled.The URL is updated every time a photo is uploaded and reflects the most recent photo. If a newer photo is uploaded, the URL returned for an older photo isn’t guaranteed to return a photo. Query this field for the URL of the most recent photo. This field is available in API version 20.0 and later.

DigestFrequency.title: Chatter Email Highlights Frequency
DigestFrequency.description: Required. The send frequency of the user’s Chatter personal email digest. The valid values are: D = Daily W = Weekly N = Never The default value is D.

DefaultGroupNotificationFrequency.title: Default Notification Frequency when Joining Groups
DefaultGroupNotificationFrequency.description: Required. The default frequency for sending the user's Chatter group email notifications when the user joins groups. The valid values are: P—Email on every post D—Daily digests W—Weekly digests N—Never The default value is N. For Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Edition organizations that existed before API version 22.0, the default value remains D.This field is available in API version 21.0 and later.

JigsawImportLimitOverride.title: Data.com Monthly Addition Limit
JigsawImportLimitOverride.description: The Data.com user’s monthly addition limit. The value must be between zero and the organization’s monthly addition limit. Label is Data.com Monthly Addition Limit. This field is available in API version 27.0 and later.

IsPrmSuperUser.title: Is Partner Super User
IsPrmSuperUser.description: Available for partner portal users only. Indicates whether the user has super user access in the partner portal (true) or not (false).

BannerPhotoUrl.title: Url for banner photo
BannerPhotoUrl.description: The URL for the user's banner photo. This field is available in API version 36.0 and later.

SmallBannerPhotoUrl.title: Url for IOS banner photo
SmallBannerPhotoUrl.description: The URL for the small user profile banner photo.

MediumBannerPhotoUrl.title: Url for Android banner photo
MediumBannerPhotoUrl.description: The URL for the medium-sized user profile banner photo.

IsProfilePhotoActive.title: Has Profile Photo
IsProfilePhotoActive.description: Indicates whether a user has a profile photo (true) or not (false). This field is available in API version 36.0 and later.

data.label: User
